<br>
SZ is a server in flux. A testing grounds of PvP for Verant. After weeks of reading complaints/whines/flames about green farming, bottom feeding, or whatever label you want to slap on it, they &quot;fucked up yet another patch&quot; by tipping the scales in favor of those who have been beat down relentlessly while trying to level up to a respectable and viable position; those who have been CC'd while simply travelling between towns to buy their new spells and songs.  The dev team is probably dying of laughter over the things they've read in the last few days.<br>
<br>
Sure it's temporary, but from the posts I've read here, it's working as intended: the farmers are crying foul and tucking tail. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=FAEBD7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/udiako.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Diako</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tavern Regular</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/17/01 10:29:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why the patch was intentional...</span><hr size=1> As much as I agree with you, being Good... I have been feeling the pain....<br>
<br>
Duck for Cover...  They are going to Flame you for this one....<br>
<br>
/em Ducks under a pebble <p><b>Diako Kronanta<br>
