<br>
Unfortunate they will change it in some ways, since it sounds like they went a bit far with it. In fact I'm sure they went too far with it--hell I resisted ae bard fear naked with no elemental playing from a bard that wasn't even smart enough to use a horn to play it--hint to evil bard at RE/gorge zone put some points in brass and practice it using your 18th song...(oh yeah..um, and do this by a guard so one pks ya--<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
I was level 12 to his 26+.<br>
<br>
No...he wasnt meleeiing or throwing in dots either, just standing there while his melees beat on everything. Perhaps he was afk...but I guess now isn't the time for a critique of his style, which was weak though his form was excellent. Regardless I hate him on principle.<br>
<br>
Look, this isn't rz or tz, I know that, there isnt a rule that says you &quot;have&quot; to beat on even cons. There's no rule that says you cant kills greens that are in your way either. But making the killing of greens your sole raison d'etre--and all teams do this, please get over yourselves about that--doesn't &quot;prune&quot; the population, it doesn't &quot;dishearten&quot; your enemy, it doesn't &quot;make your team stronger.&quot; You know what it does do though? It fills up my chat window with people screaming and crying and for that, I find you to be just as annoying as the people who are dead, which is to say very.<br>
<br>
[edit], Wythe, bard of 12 songs, Bristlebane<br>
<br>
